search:Kafka + Apache Avro Schema Evolut.content:
- **Latest Kafka Streams Version**: 3.4.0
- **Latest Avro Version**: 1.11.2
- **Key Config Options**:
  - `key.deserializer`: `org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.Serdes.StringDeserializer`
  - `value.deserializer`: `io.confluent.kafka.serializers.KafkaAvroDeserializer`
  - `schema.registry.url`: URL of the Confluent Schema Registry

- **CLI Commands**:
  ```bash
  kafka-topics.sh --create --topic CustomerTopic --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --replication-factor 1 --partitions 3
  kafka-topics.sh --create --topic BalanceTopic --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --replication-factor 1 --partitions 3
  kafka-topics.sh --create --topic CustomerBalanceOutput --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --replication-factor 1 --partitions 3
  ```

- **Example Code Snippet**:
  ```java
  Properties props = new Properties();
  props.put(StreamsConfig.APPLICATION_ID_CONFIG, "customer-balance-stream");
  props.put(StreamsConfig.BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS_CONFIG, "localhost:9092");
  props.put(StreamsConfig.DEFAULT_KEY_SERDE_CLASS_CONFIG, Serdes.String().getClass());
  props.put(StreamsConfig.DEFAULT_VALUE_SERDE_CLASS_CONFIG, KafkaAvroDeserializer.class);
  props.put("schema.registry.url", "http://localhost:8081");

  StreamsBuilder builder = new StreamsBuilder();
  KStream<String, GenericRecord> customerStream = builder.stream("CustomerTopic");
  KStream<String, GenericRecord> balanceStream = builder.stream("BalanceTopic");

  // Process streams and produce output
  customerStream.join(balanceStream,
    (customer, balance) -> {
      // Process logic here
      return new GenericData.Record(outputSchema);
    },
    JoinWindows.of(Duration.ofMinutes(1)),
    StreamJoined.with(Serdes.String(), KafkaAvroSerde.class, KafkaAvroSerde.class)
  ).to("CustomerBalanceOutput", Produced.with(Serdes.String(), KafkaAvroSerializer.class));

  KafkaStreams streams = new KafkaStreams(builder.build(), props);
  streams.start();
  ```
